  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a full kettle, then peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them in half</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into chunks on the diagonal</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> by squashing it with the side of a knife (keep the skin on!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1710949428515-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1710949428515-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1710949428515-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1710949428515-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1710949428515-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and <strong>sliced carrots </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min, then drain over a large bowl and save the water for later, then shake them around the colander to fluff up the edges, reserve the pot</p><p>While the potatoes are cooking, strip the <strong>thyme</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1710949433771-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1710949433771-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1710949433771-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1710949433771-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1710949433771-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>free range chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a clean chopping board and slice through the thickest part of the chicken being careful not to cut all the way through to the other side, then open them out like a book</p><p>Cover with<strong> cling film </strong>and bash with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>until you have an even thickness – this is your <strong>butterflied chicken</strong></p><p>Season the <strong>butterflied chicken </strong>with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>thyme </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>seasoned chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1710949442629-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1710949442629-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1710949442629-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1710949442629-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1710949442629-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes and carrots are cooked, heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>remaining thyme </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained potatoes & carrots </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 10-12 min or until golden and crispy, turning occasionally for even colouring</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1710949448558-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1710949448558-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1710949448558-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1710949448558-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1710949448558-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side until golden</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
