      "instruction": "<p>While the gravy is thickening, trim, then chop the <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved green beans</strong> to the reserved pot and cover them with<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining reserved water</strong> (just enough to cover them)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender, then drain and stir through a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>",
